@startuml
title Графовое расширение (GraphRAG) в системе

actor "Клиент системы" as Client
participant "FastAPI\nPOST /v1/documents/bulk" as IndexAPI
participant "FastAPI\nPOST /v1/search" as SearchAPI
participant "FastAPI\nPOST /v1/ask" as AskAPI
participant "SearchService" as Service
participant "Neo4jAdapter" as Neo
participant "LLMService" as LLM
database "Neo4j" as NeoDb
participant "Ollama API\n/api/generate" as Ollama

group 1) Формирование графа при индексации
  Client -> IndexAPI: POST /v1/documents/bulk {items}
  IndexAPI -> Service: index_documents_bulk(payloads)
  Service -> Service: after OpenSearch success,\nselect succeeded_ids
  Service -> Neo: ingest_documents(rows for succeeded_ids)
  Neo -> Neo: normalize rows by domain graph ingest mapping
  Neo -> NeoDb: run rendered graph_ingest Cypher template
  NeoDb --> Neo: write result
  Neo --> Service: graph succeeded_ids / failed_ids
  Service --> IndexAPI: indexed, failed_ids
end

group 2) Графовое расширение в поиске
  Client -> SearchAPI: POST /v1/search {query, limit, ...}
  SearchAPI -> Service: search(...)
  Service -> Service: build lexical+vector ranking

  Service -> Neo: fetch_graph_context(item_ids, limits)
  Neo -> NeoDb: run rendered graph_context Cypher template
  NeoDb --> Neo: graph rows (or error)
  Neo --> Service: graph_context_map (may be empty)
  Service -> Service: attach payload.graph\n(connections, related_movies)\nfor matched items

  Service --> SearchAPI: SearchItem[] (with/without payload.graph)
  SearchAPI --> Client: SearchResponse
end

group 3) Использование граф-контекста в LLM-ответе
  Client -> AskAPI: POST /v1/ask {question, items}
  AskAPI -> Service: answer_from_search_items(question, items)
  Service -> LLM: answer_from_items(question, items)
  LLM -> LLM: compact graph from payload.graph\n(connections + top related_movies)
  LLM -> LLM: render prompt with context+schema
  LLM -> Ollama: POST /api/generate
  Ollama --> LLM: response
  LLM --> Service: {answer, think}
  Service --> AskAPI: {answer, think}
  AskAPI --> Client: AskResponse
end

@enduml
